<seg id="750">& dot; algorithm, the standard for directional graphs. it produces hierarchical or layered representations of aligned graphs. the algorithm places the edges in the same direction (from top to bottom or from left to right) and tries to produce as short edges as possible and as few edges as possible.</seg>
<seg id="751">The & nato; algorithm is the standard for unfinished graphs. it produces displays according to the spring spring model. the Kamada-Kawai algorithm is used, which is synonymous with statistical multi-dimensional scaling.</seg>
